@context: DemoQA Gauntlet - Comprehensive UI Elements Test. Covers forms, checkbox trees, radio buttons, dynamic web tables, multi-click buttons, select menus, and date pickers.
@title: full_ui_element_suite

# 🐾 DEMOQA GAUNTLET: The Full Elements Challenge
#
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FEATURES DEMONSTRATED:
#
#   NAVIGATE to <url>   — Loads a URL and waits for DOM settlement.
#                         Each NAVIGATE is a system keyword that bypasses
#                         heuristic scoring entirely.
#
#   WAIT <seconds>      — Hard sleep (e.g. WAIT 2). Useful when the UI
#                         needs time to render after an action. Prefer
#                         "Wait for 'Text' to be visible" for deterministic
#                         waits when possible.
#
#   EXTRACT ... into {var}
#                       — Captures text from the page into a runtime
#                         variable {alden_salary}. Reusable in later steps.
#
#   DOUBLE CLICK        — Triggers Playwright's dblclick() on the
#                         resolved element.
#
#   Multi-page test     — Each STEP navigates to a different DemoQA page,
#                         demonstrating that a single .hunt file can cover
#                         multiple pages in sequence.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 1: Text box form submission
    NAVIGATE to https://demoqa.com/text-box
    FILL 'Full Name' field with 'Ghost Manul'
    FILL 'Email' field with 'ghost@manul.ai'
    FILL 'Current Address' field with '42 Shadow Lane'
    FILL 'Permanent Address' field with '7 Phantom Street'
    CLICK the 'Submit' button
    # Separate VERIFY steps: each quoted value is asserted independently.
    VERIFY that 'Ghost Manul' is present
    VERIFY that 'ghost@manul.ai' is present

STEP 2: Checkbox tree
    NAVIGATE to https://demoqa.com/checkbox
    CLICK the 'Expand all' button
    # "checkbox for 'Home'" — the engine applies strict checkbox mode:
    # non-checkbox elements get a heavy scoring penalty.
    CHECK the checkbox for 'Home'
    WAIT 2
    VERIFY that 'You have selected' is present

STEP 3: Radio button
    NAVIGATE to https://demoqa.com/radio-button
    # "radio button for 'Impressive'" — strict radio mode, same as checkbox.
    CLICK the radio button for 'Impressive'
    VERIFY that 'Impressive' is present

STEP 4: Web tables — data extraction
    NAVIGATE to https://demoqa.com/webtables
    # EXTRACT finds the row containing 'Alden' and extracts the Salary column.
    EXTRACT the 'Salary of Alden' into {alden_salary}
    VERIFY that '2000' is present

STEP 5: Button interactions
    NAVIGATE to https://demoqa.com/buttons
    DOUBLE CLICK the 'Double Click Me' button
    VERIFY that 'You have done a double click' is present
    CLICK the 'Click Me' button
    VERIFY that 'You have done a dynamic click' is present

STEP 6: Select menu
    NAVIGATE to https://demoqa.com/select-menu
    # Select uses Playwright's select_option() for native <select> tags.
    # Falls back to click() for custom div-based dropdowns.
    SELECT 'Purple' from the 'Select Value' dropdown
    VERIFY that 'Purple' is present

STEP 7: Date picker
    NAVIGATE to https://demoqa.com/date-picker
    FILL 'Date Of Birth' field with '01/15/1990'
    VERIFY that '01/15/1990' is present

STEP 8: Navigation links
    NAVIGATE to https://demoqa.com/slider
    VERIFY that 'Slider' is present
    NAVIGATE to https://demoqa.com/links
    # "Click on the 'Home' link" — including "link" outside the quotes
    # acts as an element-type hint, boosting <a> tags in scoring.
    CLICK on the 'Home' link
DONE.
